The paper deals with the problem of learning neuro-symbolic representations for biological knowledge, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of machine learning classifiers to enable biological link prediction suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also utilizes a comprehensive biological knowledge graph, which implies that it may belong to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper deals with biomedical knowledge, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
